I89. Advocates for competition

I11(a) T4Establishment and Designation._

I12(1) T4EstablishmentK._Each executive agency has an advocate for competition.

I12(2) T4DesignationK._The head of each executive agency shall_

I13(A) designate for the executive agency and for each procuring activity of the executive agency one officer or employee serving in a position authorized for the executive agency on July 18, 1984 (other than the senior procurement executive designated pursuant to section 1702(c) of this title) to serve as the advocate for competition;

I13(B) not assign those officers or employees duties or responsibilities that are inconsistent with the duties and responsibilities of the advocates for competition; and

I13(C) provide those officers or employees with the staff or assistance necessary to carry out the duties and responsibilities of the advocate for competition, such as individuals who are specialists in engineering, technical operations, contract administration, financial management, supply management, and utilization of small and disadvantaged business concerns.

Q04

I11(b) T4Duties and FunctionsK._The advocate for competition of an executive agency shall_

I12(1) be responsible for challenging barriers to, and promoting full and open competition in, the procurement of property and services by the executive agency;

I12(2) review the procurement activities of the executive agency;

I12(3) identify and report to the senior procurement executive of the executive agency_

I13(A) opportunities and actions taken to achieve full and open competition in the procurement activities of the executive agency; and

I13(B) any condition or action which has the effect of unnecessarily restricting competition in the procurement actions of the executive agency;

Q04

I12(4) prepare and transmit to the senior procurement executive an annual report describing_

