I11(a) T4DefinitionK._In this section, the term ``Council'' has the meaning given that term in section 1301 of this title.

I11(b) T4Application._

I12(1) T4In generalK._Except as provided in paragraph (2), the requirement for adjustment under subsection (c) applies to a dollar threshold that is specified in law as a factor in defining the scope of the applicability of a policy, procedure, requirement, or restriction provided in that law to the procurement of property or services by an executive agency, as the Council determines.

I12(2) T4ExceptionsK._Subsection (c) does not apply to dollar thresholds_

I13(A) in chapter 67 of this title;

I13(B) in sections 3141 to 3144, 3146, and 3147 of title 40; or

I13(C) the United States Trade Representative establishes pursuant to title III of the Trade Agreements Act of 1979 (19 U.S.C. 2511 et seq.).

Q04

I12(3) T4Relationship to other inflation adjustment authoritiesK._This section supersedes the applicability of other provisions of law that provide for the adjustment of a dollar threshold that is adjustable under this section.

Q04

I11(c) T4Requirement for Periodic Adjustment._

I12(1) T4Baseline constant dollar valueK._For purposes of paragraph (2), the baseline constant dollar value for a dollar threshold_

I13(A) in effect on October 1, 2000, that was first specified in a law that took effect on or before October 1, 2000, is the October 1, 2000, constant dollar value of that dollar threshold; and

I13(B) specified in a law that takes effect after October 1, 2000, is the constant dollar value of that threshold as of the effective date of that dollar threshold pursuant to that law.

Q04

I12(2) T4AdjustmentK._On October 1 of each year evenly divisible by 5, the Council shall adjust each acquisition-related dollar threshold provided by law, as described in subsection (b)(1), to the baseline constant dollar value of that threshold.

I12(3) T4Exclusive means of adjustmentK._A dollar threshold adjustable under this section shall be adjusted only as provided in this section.

Q04

I11(d) T4PublicationK._The Council shall publish a notice of the adjusted dollar thresholds under this section in the Federal Register. The thresholds take effect on the date of publication.

I11(e) T4CalculationK._An adjustment under this section shall be_

I12(1) calculated on the basis of changes in the Consumer Price Index for all-urban consumers published monthly by the Secretary of Labor; and

I12(2) rounded, in the case of a dollar threshold that on the day before the adjustment is_

I13(A) less than $10,000, to the nearest $500;

I13(B) not less than $10,000, but less than $100,000, to the nearest $5,000;

I13(C) not less than $100,000, but less than $1,000,000, to the nearest $50,000; and

I13(D) $1,000,000 or more, to the nearest $500,000.

Q04

I11(f) T4Petition for Inclusion of Omitted Threshold._

