I11(d) T4Requirements Relating to Database Information._

I12(1) T4Direct input and updateK._The Administrator of General Services shall design and maintain the database in a manner that allows the appropriate Federal agency officials to directly input and update information in the database relating to actions that the officials have taken with regard to contractors or grant recipients.

I12(2) T4Timeliness and accuracyK._The Administrator of General Services shall develop policies to require_

I13(A) the timely and accurate input of information into the database;

I13(B) the timely notification of any covered person when information relevant to the person is entered into the database; and

I13(C) opportunities for any covered person to submit comments pertaining to information about the person for inclusion in the database.

Q04

I12(3) T4Information on corporationsK._The information in the database on a person that is a corporation shall, to the extent practicable, include information on any parent, subsidiary, or successor entities to the corporation in a manner designed to give the acquisition officials using the database a comprehensive understanding of the performance and integrity of the corporation in carrying out Federal contracts and grants.

