I89. Definitions

I11In this chapter:

I12(1) T4AdministratorK._The term ``Administrator'' means the Administrator for Federal Procurement Policy appointed pursuant to section 1102 of this title.

I12(2) T4Agency board or agency board of contract appealsK._The term ``agency board'' or ``agency board of contract appeals'' means_

I13(A) the Armed Services Board;

I13(B) the Civilian Board;

I13(C) the board of contract appeals of the Tennessee Valley Authority; or

I13(D) the Postal Service Board established under section 7105(d)(1) of this titleK.

Q04

I12(3) T4Agency headK._The term ``agency head'' means the head and any assistant head of an executive agency. The term may include the chief official of a principal division of an executive agency if the head of the executive agency so designates that chief official.

I12(4) T4Armed services boardK._The term ``Armed Services Board'' means the Armed Services Board of Contract Appeals established under section 7105(a)(1) of this title.

I12(5) T4Civilian boardK._The term ``Civilian Board'' means the Civilian Board of Contract Appeals established under section 7105(b)(1) of this title.

I12(6) T4Contracting officerK._The term ``contracting officer''_

I13(A) means an individual who, by appointment in accordance with applicable regulations, has the authority to make and administer contracts and to make determinations and findings with respect to contracts; and

I13(B) includes an authorized representative of the contracting officer, acting within the limits of the representative's authority.

Q04

I12(7) T4ContractorK._The term ``contractor'' means a party to a Federal Government contract other than the Federal Government.

I12(8) T4Executive agencyK._The term ``executive agency'' means_

I13(A) an executive department as defined in section 101 of title 5;

I13(B) a military department as defined in section 102 of title 5;

I13(C) an independent establishment as defined in section 104 of title 5, except that the term does not include the Government Accountability Office; and

I13(D) a wholly owned Government corporation as defined in section 9101(3) of title 31.

Q04

I12(9) T4Misrepresentation of factK._The term ``misrepresentation of fact'' means a false statement of substantive fact, or conduct that leads to a belief of a substantive fact material to proper understanding of the matter in hand, made with intent to deceive or mislead.

