I89. Definitions

I11In this chapter:

I12(1) T4Contracting agencyK._The term ``contracting agency'', when used with respect to a prime contractor, means a department, agency, or establishment of the Federal Government that enters into a prime contract with a prime contractor.

I12(2) T4KickbackK._The term ``kickback'' means any money, fee, commission, credit, gift, gratuity, thing of value, or compensation of any kind that is provided to a prime contractor, prime contractor employee, subcontractor, or subcontractor employee to improperly obtain or reward favorable treatment in connection with a prime contract or a subcontract relating to a prime contract.

I12(3) T4PersonK._The term ``person'' means a corporation, partnership, business association of any kind, trust, joint-stock company, or individual.

I12(4) T4Prime contractK._The term ``prime contract'' means a contract or contractual action entered into by the Federal Government to obtain supplies, materials, equipment, or services of any kind.

I12(5) T4Prime contractorK._The term ``prime contractor'' means a person that has entered into a prime contract with the Federal Government.

I12(6) T4Prime contractor employeeK._The term ``prime contractor employee'' means an officer, partner, employee, or agent of a prime contractor.

I12(7) T4SubcontractK._The term ``subcontract'' means a contract or contractual action entered into by a prime contractor or subcontractor to obtain supplies, materials, equipment, or services of any kind under a prime contract.

I12(8) T4SubcontractorK._The term ``subcontractor''_

I13(A) means a person, other than the prime contractor, that offers to furnish or furnishes supplies, materials, equipment, or services of any kind under a prime contract or a subcontract entered into in connection with the prime contract; and

I13(B) includes a person that offers to furnish or furnishes general supplies to the prime contractor or a higher tier subcontractor.

Q04

I12(9) T4Subcontractor employeeK._The term ``subcontractor employee'' means an officer, partner, employee, or agent of a subcontractor.

